<p>Philosopher <a href="https://philpeople.org/profiles/krushil-watene" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Krushil Watene</a> and archaeologist <a href="https://profiles.auckland.ac.nz/t-ladefoged/publications" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Thegn Ladefoged</a>, both of the University of Auckland, have won a major grant from the Marsden Fund of The Royal Society Te Apārangi (New Zealand) for work on the persistence and flourishing of indigenous communities.<span id="more-55624"></span></p>
<div id="attachment_55625" style="width: 751px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-55625" class=" wp-image-55625" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/te-waru-rewiri-kura-a-construction-of-the-past-1024x691.jpeg" alt="" width="741" height="500" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/te-waru-rewiri-kura-a-construction-of-the-past-1024x691.jpeg 1024w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/te-waru-rewiri-kura-a-construction-of-the-past-300x202.jpeg 300w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/te-waru-rewiri-kura-a-construction-of-the-past-768x518.jpeg 768w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/te-waru-rewiri-kura-a-construction-of-the-past-400x270.jpeg 400w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/te-waru-rewiri-kura-a-construction-of-the-past.jpeg 1475w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 741px) 100vw, 741px" /><p id="caption-attachment-55625" class="wp-caption-text">[&#8220;A Construction of the Past&#8221; by Kura Te Waru Rewiri]</p></div>The project, “Ko te Rerenga o te Matuku (The Flight of the Bittern)” brings together archaeology, philosophy, history, the cultural knowledge of the Ngāti Manu hapū (tribal community), and the concept of <em>collective continuance </em>(owed to <a href="https://seas.umich.edu/research/faculty/kyle-whyte">Kyle Whyte</a>) &#8220;to understand how resilience and recovery have developed through lived experience,&#8221; according to a press release.</p>
<p>&#8220;Ngāti Manu’s narratives and aspirations will guide each stage of the research, connecting oral record and archaeological evidence with contemporary issues of place and wellbeing.</p>
<p>Narratives and aspirations will guide each stage of the research, connecting oral record and archaeological evidence with contemporary issues of place and wellbeing,&#8221; it continues.</p>
<p>The grant is for NZ $853,000 (approximately US $484,000)</p>
<p>You can learn about the other Marsden Fund Awards <a href="https://www.royalsociety.org.nz/what-we-do/funds-and-opportunities/marsden/awarded-grants/marsden-fund-awards-2025/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p><p>The post <a href="https://dailynous.com/2025/11/17/large-grant-for-philosopher-archaeologist-indigenous-community-flourishing/">Large Grant for Philosopher & Archaeologist on Indigenous Community Flourishing</a> first appeared on <a href="https://dailynous.com">Daily Nous</a>.</p>